comment_regular_data.body:
> The normal way of expanding a visual selection is a{motion/textobj} or i{motion/textobj}

Just to mention this here: The plan is to upstream incremental selection over the treesitter syntax tree from nvim-treesitter's `incremental_selection` (suitably pruned and cleaned up), in the form of `an{ode}` and `in{ode}` (mnemonic, exact name tbd).

The "grow/shrink selection" mapping is simply sugar on top of that (or whatever the LSP textobject is), in my opinion.
